response.original_title: Super Why: Cinderella and Other Fairytale Adventures
response.overview: The Super Readers work with Prince Charming to find Cinderella. It's up to the team to think creatively and save the day! Then they'll use Alphabet Power, Spelling Power, and Word Power, to help the characters in Snow White learn to stop and think. And, in The Boy Who Cried Wolf, everyone learns the importance of trust. Make reading an adventure and use the Power to Read to change the story in these classic tales.
response.title: Super Why: Cinderella and Other Fairytale Adventures
